1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:08,771
So basically, kafka 2.8+ introduced KRaft (Kafka Raft) — a built-in consensus mechanism that eliminates the ZooKeeper dependency entirely.

2
00:00:08,721 --> 00:00:14,653
In KRaft mode, a quorum of broker nodes use the Raft protocol to manage cluster metadata directly.

3
00:00:14,653 --> 00:00:20,298
As of Kafka 3.3, KRaft is production-ready, and ZooKeeper mode is deprecated.

